I read your articles. Found them rather interesting. Some good questions asked and it's obvious you did a great deal of research. Trouble is that I think you may have selected the wrong forum to submit them to. It's true we do have a wealth of political and ethical material here but all of it has some relevance to nuclear technology and spaceflight. I would suggest you try another news site. If you feel I might be wrong then you are welcome to submit your articles directly to the webmaster here. I'm just a lowly admin you see. If you should decide, after looking around the place, you might like to do a political paper concerning nuclear space stuff, then I'm sure Zaphod would be keen to take a look at it.<br>
For example, something on the politics of reactor rockets maybe. Reagan tried to unshelve them for his 'Star Wars' project and Bush would need a similar launch device to get his own 'Defence Shield' up. That's only an example. I sense you are primarily interested in politics and world events so this might be a good one for you. Earthshaking international changes would include a new generation of controversial launcher essential to the Defence Shield. Not many people realise that nuclear power would be vital for the success of any defence program involving massive payload to LEO. Just look at the ISS and then ask yourself how else it could be done. Look up 'Project Rover' and 'Timberwind' if I have stirred your interest. <p>
